# Code Style

## Quotes

Always use single quotes for strings. Double quotes only inside JSX attribute values.

```ts
// ❌ BAD
import { foo } from "./foo";
const label = "hello";

// ✅ GOOD
import { foo } from './foo';
const label = 'hello';
```

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — double quotes inside JSX attributes are fine
<input placeholder="Your answer…" />
```

## Other conventions

- No semicolons unless required to disambiguate
- `const` over `let` wherever possible
- Explicit return types on exported functions
- No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow
